question: Tī ' fiscal 2022 kah 2023 ' kî-kan, hō͘-lîn hāng-bo̍k ê che̍k-tōa thàu-chu̍t sī sé-hāng che?
answer: long-term debt including current portionexcluding capital lease obligations ( 1 )

question: Choah-sī hiah-ê "operating lease obligations" kap "capital lease obligations" lóng-chóng tsiam-tuì tio̍h "fiscal 2020 and 2021" ê sî-kan, tsiah-ê tâi-kim lóng-tsóng sī kúi-khoán?
Tī sèng 2019 nî àn-sò͘ ài hō͘ ê kuan-hē lūi tang-tiong, sióh-ê sióh-tiám ê hō͘ chîⁿ ê lūi, i ê "kî-āu" ài hō͘ ê chîⁿ sī toh-chē chîⁿ?
Chiu-siâu 'operating lease obligations' ê hū-khuànn chhuat-tián tī só͘-chāi ha̍p-suan kî-kan?
answer: 'Operating lease obligations' ê hū-khuànn sī chiàn-chêng ê chhuat-tián. I khai-sí tī 2019 nî ê $132.1 pah-bān, tī 2020-2021 kî-kan tòe tio̍h $199.9 pah-bān, liáu-āu soá kàu 2022-2023 nî ê $118.4 pah-bān, kah chòe-āu chi̍t pái $165.4 pah-bān sī iâⁿ-lâi. Chit ê kóa-chāi sī kóng chin chē choán-chè tī chìn-liân, kah in tòat-tòat ê sî-chūn pí-kàu, kán-ná ū khah-chió ê tn̂g-kî kim-iok.

question: Chiah-chū bē-lâi ê goā-sè chù-tiāu lūi-hāng, to̍t-chóng su-iàu hāi ê chi̍h-chúi bē-kúi $1000 pah-bān, jî-chhiáⁿ "kàu-tâi" ê chi̍h-chúi koh-khah-kúi $150 pah-bān?
'tsng-kî tsè-kim' ê chóng-pài tī hit āu hāi ê phah-sǹg chiàm toh-tsóng kài chē sîng？
Nāi-sū, nā chēⁿ chio̍h-chiap ê chāi-pau-bu̍t lóng hō͘ siau-tiāu, chāi-pau-bu̍t ê sin-ê "chiap-chiap chāi-chiap" choân-pō͘ choân-pō͘ ê "kang-chok-koan" tī "2019 chiuⁿ-kî" ê tâi-tô͘ sī siáⁿ-miâ ê?
Jīn-pái hō͘-chāi ê chu-liāu, 'tn̂g-kî chè-chha' kap 'chòe-bóe ê che̍k-bo̍k kap pa̍t-ê' ê tōa-bo̍k ê kòa-piàn, siáⁿ-mi̍h sī chin chha-pia̍t ê khu-pia̍t?
answer: In-ê chāi tōa-bo̍k ê se̍h-sî-khì, ū chin chái chha-pia̍t ê koan-hē. 'Tn̂g-kî chè-chha' sī chin tiōng-chōe tī āu-che̍h, siōng-bōe ê chāi lóng-chóng ê ( $3136.6M / $6039.0M ) sī tī 'āu-āu' ê sî-kî. Pí-lâi, 'chòe-bóe ê che̍k-bo̍k kap pa̍t-ê' sī chin tiōng-chōe tī chá-che̍h, siōng-bōe ê chāi lóng-chóng ê ( $1676.6M / $2210.5M ) sī tī siōng-chá ê sî-kî, 2019 ê hong-lí nî, chí-chāi che sī chú-iàu ê té-kî che̍k-bo̍k.

question: E5 cel ê tiat ê kiat-kò, 'fiscal 2022 kah 2023' ê tsong-su, án-chóaⁿ hō͘ piáⁿ ê sêng-hun lâi thun-siāu?
answer: E5 cel ê tiat ($ 1587.0) sī chi̍t hāng tâng-sî hō͘ siu-kòe ê sì chióng hū-chek lūi-hêng ê 'fiscal 2022 kah 2023' nî-tō͘ ê chiâⁿ-bīn ê siu-kòe chiah-ê ê thun-siāu tāi-chì: $1351.0 (E1), $118.4 (E2), $2.7 (E3), kah $114.9 (E4).

question: Chiah chiah bo-liap ê kî-kan tō-sī siáⁿ-chi̍t ê tī cheng-chha̍h chha-ê luī-pia̍h ê tāi-chì, hām siáⁿ-chiáⁿ chha-ê bo-liap ê goân-in?
answer: Sió-li̍k 2019 sī chi̍t ê te̍k-tì. I ê chóng-kiōng $2540.3 pah-bān-gô͘ tùi āu-ê nn̄g ê kî-kan ($1255.5M hām $1587.0M) khah tōa chin chē. Chit ê te̍k-tì sī chin chú-iàu sī 'bōe-chè ê cheng-chi̍t hām pa̍t-chiá' ê lūi-pia̍h, ū chi̍t ê hui-siông tōa ê hêng-hō $1676.6 pah-bān-gô͘ chòe tī hit tang, sī hit ê kî-kan chóng-kiōng ê tāi-khài 66%.

question: Tī 2019 niáⁿ kap 2020–2021 ê lúi-kî lāi-bīn, choân-pō͘ chū-khoán chek-jīm (chhiok-ha̍h kap chiūⁿ-tiāⁿ chū-khoán) ê chóng-hē-sò͘ sī kúi-ā-ê pah-bān ê gîn-phiò?
